//! Networking primitives for IP communication.
//!
//! This module provides platform-independent network types for working with
//! IP addresses, socket addresses, and network I/O buffers.
//!
//! # IP Addresses
//!
//! - [`Ipv4Addr`] - A 32-bit IPv4 address (e.g., `192.168.1.1`)
//! - [`Ipv6Addr`] - A 128-bit IPv6 address (e.g., `::1`)
//! - [`IpAddr`] - An enum that can hold either IPv4 or IPv6
//!
//! # Socket Addresses
//!
//! Socket addresses combine an IP address with a port number:
//!
//! - [`SocketAddrV4`] - IPv4 address + port
//! - [`SocketAddrV6`] - IPv6 address + port + flow info + scope ID
//! - [`SocketAddr`] - An enum that can hold either V4 or V6
//!
//! # Buffer Management
//!
//! Efficient buffer types for network I/O:
//!
//! - [`Buffer`] - A growable byte buffer with capacity management
//! - [`BufferView`] - A zero-copy view into byte data
//! - [`BufferPool`] - Pre-allocated buffer pool for reuse
//!
//! # Platform Abstraction
//!
//! Low-level socket operations (in [`sys`] module):
//!
//! - [`RawSocket`] - Platform-specific socket handle
//! - Socket creation, binding, listening, connecting
//! - Non-blocking I/O support
//!
//! # Examples
//!
//! ## Working with IP Addresses
//!
//! ```tml
//! use std::net::{Ipv4Addr, Ipv6Addr, IpAddr}
//!
//! // Create IPv4 addresses
//! let localhost = Ipv4Addr::new(127, 0, 0, 1)
//! let private = Ipv4Addr::new(192, 168, 1, 1)
//!
//! // Use predefined constants
//! let loopback = Ipv4Addr::LOCALHOST
//! let any = Ipv4Addr::UNSPECIFIED
//!
//! // Check address properties
//! assert(localhost.is_loopback())
//! assert(private.is_private())
//! ```
//!
//! ## Working with Socket Addresses
//!
//! ```tml
//! use std::net::{SocketAddr, SocketAddrV4, Ipv4Addr}
//!
//! // Create a socket address
//! let addr = SocketAddrV4::new(Ipv4Addr::LOCALHOST, 8080)
//!
//! // Access components
//! let ip = addr.ip()
//! let port = addr.port()
//!
//! // Or use the unified SocketAddr type
//! let socket: SocketAddr = SocketAddr::V4(addr)
//! ```
//!
//! ## Using Buffers
//!
//! ```tml
//! use std::net::buffer::{Buffer, BufferPool}
//!
//! // Use a buffer pool for efficient allocation
//! let pool = BufferPool::new(16, 4096)
//! let mut buf = pool.get()
//!
//! // Write and read data
//! buf.write_bytes(b"Hello")
//! let view = buf.as_view()
//!
//! // Return to pool
//! pool.put(buf)
//! ```
//!
//! # TCP Networking
//!
//! TCP (Transmission Control Protocol) types for reliable connections:
//!
//! - [`TcpListener`] - Listens for incoming TCP connections
//! - [`TcpStream`] - A connected TCP socket for reading and writing
//! - [`TcpBuilder`] - Builder pattern for TCP socket configuration
//!
//! # UDP Networking
//!
//! UDP (User Datagram Protocol) types for connectionless communication:
//!
//! - [`UdpSocket`] - A UDP socket for sending and receiving datagrams
//! - [`UdpBuilder`] - Builder pattern for UDP socket configuration
//!
//! # Module Structure
//!
//! - [`ip`] - IP address types (`Ipv4Addr`, `Ipv6Addr`, `IpAddr`)
//! - [`socket`] - Socket address types (`SocketAddrV4`, `SocketAddrV6`, `SocketAddr`)
//! - [`parser`] - Parsing utilities for addresses
//! - [`error`] - Network error types (`NetError`, `NetErrorKind`)
//! - [`buffer`] - Buffer management (`Buffer`, `BufferView`, `BufferPool`)
//! - [`sys`] - Platform abstraction layer for sockets
pub mod ip
pub mod socket
